Bellona Plateau, New Caledonia, 800-923 m depth (
Pante and France 2010
).

No whole colony was obtained, thus the description was based on a picture (Figure 
19A
) and a few frozen fragments. Colony ca. 50 cm long and 11 cm wide with dendritic holdfast ca. 12 cm long. Main stem more zigzagging. Branching sequences unknown. Branches subdivided dichotomously, up to sixth order with distance between adjacent branches 10-25 mm. Polyps cylindrical, or with an expanded body base and obviously narrow neck, 1.0-2.5 mm long and 0.5-2.5 mm wide at bases, with tentacles up to 1 mm long (Figure 
19B-G
).
